view in terms sensitive to the historical and political contexts in which the practice persists. Distinguished commentators question some of the claims made in the essays, and offer their own perspectives on Marburys importance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh1 aBloch, Susan Low, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Stephen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Vicki C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReed, Douglas S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeidman, Louis Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherry, Suzanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrauss, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTushnet, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362543340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503625433423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503625433/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles